detailedReviews.author: Kevin Lehman
detailedReviews.text:
I stopped in to try a new place as I do home health and drive all over the place. I always make it a habit to try a new pizza place for lunch when I can.

I stopped in here for a late lunch at 4:08 p.m. I asked if there was any lunch specials and I was promptly told it ends at 4:00. This is by the lady who was on the phone and seemed a bit annoyed that she had to hang up to take my order. She was not young and I assumed likely the owner.  Now this is my first time in this place and I'm already getting sort of a bad taste in my mouth about the attitude toward customers. It may have been late for your lunch special but it was still lunch for me as I was extremely busy that day. There was no one else in the place and almost an entire pie sitting there for slices.  Probably would have been a smarter move to still give me the special and leave me thinking it's a nice place that I would come back to. Instead, I walked out and said I would never walk back in there again. A silly move for just a few dollars. The pizza was good but not worth the atmosphere and service.

It's unfortunate because I like to support small locally owned businesses but you have to be better to your customers if you want to compete and survive.  You only get one chance at a first impression.  Oh well ü§∑

detailedReviews.author: Still Hopeful
detailedReviews.text: I've lived near this pizza restaurant for about 6 years now. Angela's Pizza is always hot, fresh and delicious every time I place a pizza order pickup. The pizza is perfectly hand tossed thickness with a crispy crust. Oh!! My favorite because it's differently uniquely OUTSTANDING is the chicken-bacon-ranch!! Omg, I tried 2 slices for lunch one weekend, and I'm hooked. It's my favorite now! Highly recommend when you want great pizza takeout. They also have Italian entrees, too!

The incredibly low score was for the chicken Philly style sub no mushrooms (it was so soggy full of oil & little flavor my husband tossed the other half) and i ordered the Pasta bolognese (omg it was just so gross tasting, it was like can of wet doggie food & penne..not palatable, do not order it..never ever).
Both dishes were absolutely terrible sadly.
This place used to be so goooooood, this was a pre covid gem üíé but now....epic fall from grace.
The Pizza is the ONLY thing I can safely recommend, they used to be very consistent but now sometimes it's a major hit or a miss with the pizza sadly..(sometimes the pizza is so fresh & good and sometimes it taste old reheated).
Overall this used to be our favorite pizza place but the food quality is now so questionable at times and the other items offered (pastas subs) are just not good.

Stick to the hit or miss pizza, go in person so you can see/inspect your pizza, delivery can be extremely tricky as to whether or not you are getting a fresh or stale pie.
